Show HN: Finally, a Simple TypeScript ESM Packager
text:
Hey HN!

This post isn't as big as some others, but I'd like to share my tools for working with TypeScript and NPM.

If you've ever published a TypeScript library to NPM, you're probably familiar with the horrors of dealing with ESM

I've yearned for a small library to make TypeScript packages as simple as possible, without getting a bundler like ESBuild or Webpack involved. The project's readme goes into the horrible details of how strange and bizarro TypeScript's module systems have become. This NPM package has fixed most of my issues and I would love for everyone to benefit from it.

If you've ever experienced this madness, please kvetch here and maybe we can make this library obsolete by TypeScript 6!

Ask HN: Is the site font on mobile bigger suddenly?
text:
Edit: I'm specifically talking about landscape orientation. Everything seems the same in portrait.

Something seemed off today so I compared it with a snapshot of the front page from Feb 2, https://web.archive.org/web/20230202010428/https://news.ycombinator.com/. Font size on mobile seems bigger on my phone, but I'm fairly confident I've made no changes locally.

The larger font is somewhat throwing me off and is making it harder to read the site.

Ask HN: Science Fiction books that predict where ChatGPT might lead us?
text:
What is AI going to do to humanity? Is it going to take over the world and destroy us, just like we destroy an ant hill when we build a road? Is it going to make us dumb, because nobody will be able to right code, distinguish fact from fiction, etc.?

I guess there must be books that have explored these questions long before ChatGPT. Which ones do you think are the most interesting and relevant to the current developments, questions and fears? Or are the most thought provoking?

Thanks!
